ipperhost-233x300.png.webp 233w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" srcset=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/flipperhost.png.webp 300w, https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/flipperhost-233x300.png.webp 233w\" data-was-processed=\"true\"></a></p><p>Ceko from <a href=\"http://www.flipperhost.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Flipper Host</a> brings us a new KVM offer!&nbsp; Not only do they have four locations on two continents to choose from, not only do they take a ton of payment methods, not only are they giving an annual discount, and not only are their prices pretty sweet, but\u2026they also have an adorable mascot.&nbsp; How can you say no to that face?!?&nbsp; It\u2019s the flip-flops (get it?) that really seal the deal for me.</p><p><a href=\"http://www.flipperhost.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Flipper Host</a> has service in Los Angeles, Miami, New York, and Amsterdam.&nbsp; Their monthly price is nice at $3.90 for a 1GB KVM, but you can drop that to $3.33 a month if you pay annually.&nbsp; You\u2019d think 2GB would be $6.66 but\u2026nope!&nbsp; Only $4.16 on an annual contract.&nbsp; Woot!</p><p>They\u2019re an Albanian company (registration L71327003F) and their WHOIS is public.&nbsp; You can find their <a href=\"https://www.flipperhost.com/tos.php\">TOS docs</a> on their web site.&nbsp; They accept Paypal, 2Checkout, Credit Cards (All Types), Alipay, Skrill, Unionpay, Yandex.Money, Boleto Brasil, WebMoney, QIWI and Bitcoin, which I think is about every payment form known to mankind.</p><p>If you decide to jump in the pool with <a href=\"http://www.flipperhost.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Flipper Host</a>,&nbsp;the LEB community would love to hear about your experience in the comments section below!</p><p><strong>Here\u2019s what they had to say:&nbsp;</strong></p><p><em>\u201cFlipperHost is a privately owned